               <head>Mavahib-i ʻAliyah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mavāhib-i ʻalīyah by Ḥusayn ibn ʻAlī Vāʻiẓ Kāshifī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85072967 http://lccn.loc.gov/n2007204421" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15584-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100106528506.0x000001 viaf_90770167">Ḥusayn ibn ʻAlī Vāʻiẓ Kāshifī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100106528506.0x000001 viaf_90770167" type="supplied">حسين بن علی واعظ کاشفى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_253">Mavāhib-i ʻalīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_253">مواهب علية</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The second and last volume of a manuscript of the Qur’ānic commentary in Persian by Kamāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn ibn ‘Alī Vā‘iẓ Kāshifī (d. 910/1499-1500), also known as <title>Tafsīr-i Ḥusaynī</title>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Begins with the opening of <title>Sūrat Maryam</title> (XIX). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Other contents: f. 1r, owner’s inscription praising God and blessing the Prophet; f. 335r, three small number squares in margin, probably talismanic; f. 335v, two circular seal impressions, both almost completely obscured. </p>
                        <p>Copied at Herat by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7689" role="scr">Khvājah Jān ibn Khvājah Khvurd</persName>. The passage containing the year of copying has been partly lost and then re-written, but the date is almost certainly <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">5 Zū l-Ḥijja 953</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">27 January 1547</date>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
